(14, 'privacy-policy', 'Privacy policy', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">General Terms and Conditions</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">General Terms and Conditions are an integral part of the Package Travel Contract concluded between the Agency as the travel organizer on one side and the Traveler as the contracting party on the other side. In addition to these General Terms, the Contract also includes the Travel Package Program. If specified by the Contract and/or the Travel Package Program, Special Terms and Conditions are also integral parts of the Contract, in addition to these General Terms. In the event of any discrepancies between the Contract, the Travel Package Program, the Special Terms and Conditions, and these General Terms, the order of precedence shall be as follows: the Contract, the Travel Package Program, the Special Terms and Conditions, and finally, the General Terms.</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">These General Terms apply only to package tours where the Agency is the organizer. Therefore, these General Terms do not apply in cases where the Agency acts as an intermediary and/or sells services from other travel agencies. If the Agency acts as an intermediary and/or sells services from other travel agencies, the Contract will specify the responsible travel organizer, and the general terms of that organizer will apply, which the Agency will make available to the Traveler. These General Terms are considered applicable if the Contract does not specify otherwise.</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Content of the Arrangement</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">The organizer of your trip guarantees the implementation of the program as described in the arrangement program that they organize and that you have received. The content of the arrangement will be fully realized as described unless exceptional circumstances (war, riots, strikes, terrorist actions, sanitary disturbances, natural disasters, interventions by competent authorities, transport delays, epidemics, and pandemics) prevent it.</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Applications and Payments</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Applications for travel are accepted through the website or directly to the account of the Travel Organizer. When applying, the Passenger is obliged to provide accurate personal information for all passengers, i.e., persons listed in the reservation as they appear in travel documents that passengers will use during the trip or reservation consumption, and to provide all documentation necessary for the organization of the trip, all in accordance with the Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 27 April 2016 on the protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data and on the free movement of such data and the Law on the Implementation of the General Data Protection Regulation. As a travel agency, the Organizer guarantees that all documents and valid data necessary for the smooth execution of the trip will be used in accordance with legal regulations arising from the Contract and the General Terms. The Organizer is not responsible for the use or forwarding of incorrect or incomplete personal data of persons listed in the reservation, and all costs incurred due to incorrect or incomplete personal data of persons listed in the reservation will be borne by the Passenger.</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">When applying for group trips, the Passenger pays 30% of the value of the arrangement, and the remaining amount must be paid 45 days before the trip unless otherwise specified. When applying for individual trips, the Passenger pays the full amount of the arrangement according to the specified deadlines. On the day of application, the Passenger signs the contract under the title \"I am familiar with the program and terms of travel and accept them in full. I confirm that I have been offered travel insurance.\" In this way, everything mentioned in these terms becomes a legal obligation for both the Passenger and the Organizer.</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Content and Price of the Arrangement</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">The content of the arrangement includes everything that the Travel Organizer has stated in the travel program. Special services are services not included in the price of the arrangement and are therefore paid separately by the Passenger. These services should be requested when applying and are paid to the Tourism Companion or the representative of the Travel Organizer in the currency of the country where the service is provided. The prices of the arrangements are published in euros, calculated according to the prices of services in reference currencies at the exchange rate of the Organizer\'s bank on a specific day. The Organizer reserves the right to change the published prices in case of changes in accommodation prices, meals, transportation, and other services, or in case of changes in the exchange rate of the currencies that are the basis for calculating the arrangement price. For an increase in the arrangement price and additional content of up to 8%, no consent of the Passenger is required (the increase is calculated on all parts of the payment). In case of an increase greater than 8%, the Passenger has the right to terminate the contract without the obligation to compensate for the damage.</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">In case of unoccupied but reserved capacities on individual arrangements, the Organizer reserves the right to adjust the price and apply special marketing activities to facilitate the sale of unoccupied capacities. Passengers who have paid the full price of the arrangement are not entitled to a refund of the price difference.</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Categorization and Description of Services</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Offered accommodation facilities, restaurants, means of transportation, etc., are described according to the official categorization of the local tourist organization at the time of issuing the program. Standards of accommodation, meals, services, etc., in different places vary and are not comparable. The Organizer is not responsible for oral or written information that does not comply with the description of services and facilities in published programs and is obtained from a third party. If a Passenger uses a triple or quadruple room in a hotel, the hotelier usually provides a double room with an extra bed or a room with two double beds for accommodation for 4 persons. The quality of the extra (additional) bed depends entirely on the hotel. In any case, the Organizer is not responsible for the quality of the extra bed, so any dissatisfaction of the Passenger arising from these reasons cannot be the subject of a complaint.</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Change of Program</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">The travel organizer has the right to change the program if extraordinary circumstances occur (cancellations, delays, changes by local agencies) that cannot be foreseen, avoided, or eliminated. The schedule of visits during the trip is subject to change at the discretion of the tour guide. The agreed accommodation can only be replaced with accommodation in an object of the same or higher category, at the expense of the Organizer, and it will be considered that it has been fully implemented. If changes in the package travel contract or a replacement package travel contract result in a package travel of lower quality or price, the Passenger has the right to an appropriate price reduction.</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Right of the Organizer to Cancel</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">The Organizer may terminate the package travel contract before the start of the package travel and return all payments received for the package travel to the Passenger in full, without the obligation to compensate for any damage to the Passenger:</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">If extraordinary circumstances that could not be avoided prevent the Organizer from performing the contract, and if the Organizer informs the Passenger of the termination of the contract without undue delay before the start of the package travel.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">If the number of persons registered for the package travel is less than the minimum number specified in the contract, and if the Organizer informs the Passenger of the termination of the contract within the deadline specified in the contract, but not later than at least 20 days before the start of the package travel.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Passenger\'s Cancellation of the Trip</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">The Passenger has the right to cancel the trip orally or in writing before the start of the trip at the sales point where the trip was registered. In that case, the Organizer has the right to compensation for the canceled trip, and the amount of the costs is determined according to the day of the Passenger\'s cancellation and the type of travel. For all of the above, the Organizer suggests travel insurance. If the Passenger cancels the paid arrangement, the Organizer retains:</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Long-distance travel (outside Europe):</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">For cancellation up to 180 days before departure: 20%</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">For cancellation 179-90 days before departure: 70%</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">For cancellation 89-0 days before departure and after departure: 100%</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Individual travel, airline tickets, and accommodation reservations:</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">If the Passenger cancels an individual package arrangement that includes an airline ticket and accommodation, the Organizer retains 100% of the total price of the airline ticket as compensation (unless otherwise stated in the airline ticket tariff) regardless of the time until the start of the trip, and for the cancellation of hotels and other services, the conditions of the suppliers apply unless the service is reserved under special conditions that do not allow a refund (so-called non-refundable) when the service provider retains 100% of the amount of the service.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">The Organizer is obliged to ensure the implementation of services as well as the choice of service providers with the care of a good organizer and to take care of the rights and interests of the Passenger in accordance with good practices in tourism. The Organizer undertakes to provide all the services listed for a particular arrangement in the program and is responsible to the Passenger for any failure to perform services or part of the services. In these cases, the Passenger bears all additional costs.</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Passenger\'s Obligations</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">The Passenger is obliged to:</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Possess valid travel documents and provide names and surnames as they appear in the document (passport) with which they are traveling. At the request of the Organizer, the Passenger is obliged to provide a copy or original of the valid passport that they will use during the trip. For subsequent changes or additions to surnames, the Passenger bears the costs of change and modification. For long-distance travel (outside Europe), the passport must be valid for at least 6 months from the entry into the country. The cost of loss or theft of documents during the trip is borne by the Passenger. The Companion or the representative of the Organizer will assist, but subject to the smooth running of the program. If a visa is required for any trip, the Travel Organizer may, at the request of the Passenger, when possible, mediate in obtaining it for a fee. The Travel Organizer does not guarantee the issuance of visas and is not responsible for their correctness.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Vaccinate and possess certificates and documents for vaccinations for travel to countries where it is required according to the regulations of the World Health Organization. In this case, the Passenger submits a medical certificate. The lack of these documents or the invalidity of travel documents that lead to cancellation of the trip or the inability to continue the trip do not obligate the Travel Organizer and cancellation costs are charged according to Article 7.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Comply with customs and foreign exchange regulations of the Republic of Croatia, as well as the countries visited during the trip.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Adhere to the house rules in all visited facilities and cooperate with service providers in good faith.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Follow the instructions and cooperate with the Organizer, tour guide, and/or the Organizer\'s representative. When departing on a trip, the Passenger must present a document confirming the paid arrangement (original voucher, payment confirmation, copy of the payment order).</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Request and check all received travel documents (airline tickets, hotel vouchers, insurance policies, transfer schedules, etc.). If the Organizer does not receive a note from the Passenger within 24 hours (or as specified in the offer) after the documents are delivered, it will be considered that all sent documentation is valid and correct, and all costs of changes and modifications will be borne by the Passenger.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">In cases of non-compliance with these obligations, the Passenger is liable to the Organizer for any damage caused.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Luggage</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Unless otherwise specified in the travel program, the Passenger is entitled to free transportation of up to 15 kg of luggage on charter flights and up to 20 kg of luggage on regular flights. Children under 2 years of age are not entitled to free luggage transportation. Luggage is transported at the risk of the Passenger, so it is recommended to insure the luggage with an insurance company. The Travel Organizer is not responsible for damaged or lost luggage, theft of luggage or valuables in hotels (safe rental is recommended), or means of transportation. In case of damaged or lost luggage, the Passenger should report it to the carrier or the reception of the accommodation facility, depending on where the damage or loss occurred.</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Travel Insurance</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Employees of the agency where the arrangement is paid are obliged to offer the Passenger a \"package\" of travel insurance consisting of passenger health insurance during their stay abroad, luggage insurance, accident insurance, as well as insurance against the risk of the Passenger\'s trip cancellation, which are offered for both trips abroad and within our country. The insurance policy against the risk of the Passenger\'s trip cancellation must be issued no later than 48 hours from the first payment. By accepting the travel contract, which includes these travel conditions, the Passenger confirms that the \"package\" of travel insurance was offered to them. The Travel Organizer acts as an intermediary when arranging an insurance policy, and in the event of a claim against the insurance company, they cannot influence the outcome.</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Accommodation in Rooms/Apartments</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">If the Passenger has not explicitly agreed to a room/apartment with specific characteristics, they will accept any officially registered room/apartment for rent in that facility, as described in the catalog and price list. If possible, the Organizer will try to meet the Passenger\'s additional accommodation request (comfort, room orientation, floor, etc.), but cannot guarantee the fulfillment of such a request.</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">Travel Organized by Other Organizers/Tour Operators</span></p>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"> </span></h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\">For all arrangements where Desert Road for Tourism is the main organizer, these General Terms apply, except in cases where Desert Road for Tourism is an intermediary and is not the main organizer of the trip. For such arrangements, the responsible organizer will be indicated in the Contract, and the general terms of the responsible organizer apply to that trip, and Desert Road for Tourism is not responsible for the execution of travel arrangements by other organizers. By signing the contract, the Passenger fully accepts the program and travel conditions.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;vertical-align:baseline;\"> </span></p>', NULL, 'publish', NULL, NULL, 14, 1, 1, 1, '2023-09-07 10:27:23', NULL, NULL, '2023-08-31 06:12:46', '2023-09-07 10:27:23', 'normal', NULL, NULL);
